HEADWORD: Pyrrhotite
<hw>Pyr"rho*tite</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ flame-colored, fr. <?/
fire.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A bronze-colored mineral, of
metallic luster. It is a sulphide of iron, and is remarkable for being
attracted by the magnet. Called also <altname>magnetic
pyrites</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
